<page>
   <topic>FILE.LONGNAME_TO_SHORTNAME Function</topic>
   <syntax>Shortname as C = Longname_To_Shortname(C filename)</syntax>
   <arguments>
   <argument>
         <name>Shortname</name>
         <description>Fully qualified filename with path names shortened to 8 characters.
</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name>filename</name>
         <description>Fully qualified filename with standard long path names.
</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
   <description>Converts a longname to a shortname.</description>
   <discussion>
The FILE.LONGNAME_TO_SHORTNAME() method converts Windows long path names to the old style 8.3 Windows filename format.
   </discussion>
   <example><![CDATA[
? file.longname_to_shortname("C:\Databases\Expressions Test\Invoice_Header.Dbf")
= "C:\DATABA~1\EXPRES~1\Invoice_Header.Dbf"
? file.shortname_to_longname("C:\DATABA~1\EXPRES~1\Invoice_Header.Dbf")
= "C:\Databases\Expressions Test\Invoice_Header.Dbf"   
]]></example>
  
